race.comment: BLANC VISAGE (2) has been savaging the line in both runs back and is ready to peak now. Sticking to this trip suits perfectly and from her middle draw she should blend into the race beautifully before unleashing late. BRISTLER (1) bounced straight back to form last start with another brave on-pace effort. He's tough, honest, and won't fold easily if they apply pressure. Always a chance to pinch it from the front. ROUND TWO (8) was strong when resuming off a 63-day freshen, chasing hard from midfield to just miss the frame. With natural improvement, he can give this a shake. RUNAWAY BELLE (12) is another who warms up late. She hasn't won for a long time but her return run was full of merit. Worth keeping in mind.
